ial Reverses Sun Damage: What to Expect"}]]}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-inter text-[10px] tracking-wider uppercase text-gold font-semibold bg-gold/10 px-3 py-1 rounded-sm inline-block mb-4","children":"IPL / Skin"}],["$","h1",null,{"id":"blogpost-title","className":"font-playfair text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-white leading-[1.15] mb-6","children":"How IPL Photofacial Reverses Sun Damage: What to Expect"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-4 text-white/70","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-1.5 font-inter text-sm","children":[["$","svg",null,{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":24,"height":24,"viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":2,"strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","className":"lucide lucide-calendar h-3.5 w-3.5","children":[["$","path","1cmpym",{"d":"M8 2v4"}],["$","path","4m81vk",{"d":"M16 2v4"}],["$","rect","1hopcy",{"width":"18","height":"18","x":"3","y":"4","rx":"2"}],["$","path","8toen8",{"d":"M3 10h18"}],"$undefined"]}],"February 14, 2026"]}],["$","span",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-1.5 font-inter text-sm","children":[["$","svg",null,{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":24,"height":24,"viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":2,"strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","className":"lucide lucide-clock h-3.5 w-3.5","children":[["$","circle","1mglay",{"cx":"12","cy":"12","r":"10"}],["$","polyline","68esgv",{"points":"12 6 12 12 16 14"}],"$undefined"]}],"6 min read"]}]]}]]}]}]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"section-padding bg-white","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"container mx-auto px-4 md:px-8","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"grid lg:grid-cols-3 gap-16 max-w-6xl mx-auto","children":[["$","article",null,{"className":"lg:col-span-2","aria-labelledby":"blogpost-title","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"prose-blog","children":[["$","p",null,{"children":"South Florida is one of the sunniest places in the United States — which is part of what makes it so beautiful to live in. It's also why sun damage is one of the most common skin concerns we treat at Kami Aesthetics in Aventura. Years of UV exposure leave their mark: brown spots, uneven skin tone, redness, broken capillaries, and a dullness that no amount of skincare can fully reverse on its own."}],["$","p",null,{"children":["IPL photofacial with the ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"Lumenis Stellar M22"}]," is one of the most effective treatments available for reversing that damage — and the results can be dramatic."]}],["$","h2",null,{"children":"What Is IPL Photofacial?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"IPL stands for Intense Pulsed Light. Unlike a laser, which emits a single wavelength of light, IPL delivers broad-spectrum light across multiple wavelengths simultaneously. Different wavelengths target different chromophores (color-absorbing molecules) in the skin — melanin (responsible for brown spots and pigmentation) and oxyhemoglobin (responsible for redness and vascular lesions)."}],["$","p",null,{"children":"This makes IPL uniquely versatile: a single treatment session can address sun spots, age spots, rosacea, broken capillaries, and overall skin tone — all at once."}],["$","h2",null,{"children":"The Stellar M22: Why Technology Matters"}],["$","p",null,{"children":["Not all IPL devices are equal. At Kami Aesthetics, we use the ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"Lumenis Stellar M22"}]," — the most advanced IPL platform available. The key differentiator is ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"OPT™ (Optimal Pulse Technology)"}],"."]}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Traditional IPL devices deliver energy in a spike pattern: a burst of high energy at the start of each pulse that tapers off. This spike is responsible for much of the discomfort and inconsistency associated with older IPL systems — the initial energy spike can be too intense, while the tail end is too weak."}],["$","p",null,{"children":"OPT™ delivers a perfectly flat, uniform energy profile throughout each pulse. The result:"}],["$","ul",null,{"children":[["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"More consistent results"}]," — uniform energy means uniform treatment across the entire pulse"]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Less discomfort"}]," — no energy spike means a gentler sensation"]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Safer treatment"}]," — controlled energy reduces the risk of overtreatment"]}]]}],["$","p",null,{"children":["The Stellar M22 also features multiple interchangeable filters (515nm–755nm) that allow us to precisely target specific skin concerns, and the ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"ExpertFilter™"}]," system for advanced pigmentation and vascular work."]}],["$","h2",null,{"children":"What Sun Damage Actually Looks Like"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Sun damage accumulates over years and manifests in several ways:"}],["$","ul",null,{"children":[["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Solar lentigines (sun spots / age spots)"}]," — flat brown spots caused by localized melanin overproduction from UV exposure"]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Diffuse hyperpigmentation"}]," — overall uneven skin tone and dullness"]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Telangiectasia (broken capillaries)"}]," — small visible blood vessels, often on the nose and cheeks"]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Rosacea"}]," — chronic redness and flushing, often worsened by sun exposure"]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Poikiloderma"}]," — a combination of pigmentation, redness, and skin thinning, common on the neck and chest of South Florida residents"]}]]}],["$","p",null,{"children":"IPL with the Stellar M22 can address all of these in the same treatment series."}],["$","h2",null,{"children":"What to Expect: Before, During, and After"}],["$","p",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Before treatment:"}]," Avoid sun exposure and tanning for two weeks prior. Arrive with clean skin, free of makeup and skincare products. We'll apply a cool gel to the treatment area and provide protective eyewear."]}],["$","p",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"During treatment:"}]," The Stellar M22 handpiece is passed over the skin in overlapping pulses. Each pulse feels like a brief warm snap — most clients describe it as mild and very tolerable. A full-face treatment takes 20–30 minutes."]}],["$","p",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Immediately after:"}]," You'll notice mild redness and warmth, similar to a light sunburn. This typically resolves within a few hours. Brown spots will often darken initially — this is normal and expected."]}],["$","p",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Days 3–10:"}]," The darkened spots will begin to flake off, revealing clearer skin underneath. This is the treatment working as intended. Avoid picking or exfoliating during this period."]}],["$","p",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"After 7–14 days:"}]," You'll see the full initial results — clearer skin tone, reduced redness, and significantly faded brown spots. Results continue to improve with each session."]}],["$","h2",null,{"children":"How Many Sessions Do You Need?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":["For most clients treating sun damage in Aventura, we recommend a series of ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"3–5 sessions spaced 3–4 weeks apart"}],". The number depends on the severity of the damage, your skin type, and your goals."]}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After completing your initial series, maintenance sessions every 6–12 months help preserve your results — especially important in South Florida where ongoing sun exposure is unavoidable."}],["$","h2",null,{"children":"IPL vs. Other Sun Damage Treatments"}],["$","p",null,{"children":["Topical treatments like vitamin C serums and retinoids can help prevent further damage and mildly improve tone over time — but they can't remove existing sun spots or broken capillaries. Chemical peels can improve texture and mild pigmentation but don't target vascular concerns. Laser resurfacing (like ",["$","$L3",null,{"href":"/services/resurfx","className":"text-gold hover:text-gold-dark transition-colors","children":"ResurFX"}],") addresses texture and collagen but isn't optimized for pigmentation."]}],["$","p",null,{"children":"IPL is uniquely positioned to address both pigmentation and vascular concerns simultaneously — making it the most efficient single treatment for comprehensive sun damage reversal."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-warm-white border border-warm-border rounded-sm p-6 my-8","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"font-inter text-sm font-semibold text-[#1A1A1A] mb-1","children":"Ready to reverse years of sun damage?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"font-inter text-sm text-warm-gray","children":["Book your ",["$","$L3",null,{"href":"/services/ipl-photofacial","className":"text-gold hover:text-gold-dark transition-colors","children":"IPL Stellar M22 consultation"}]," at Kami Aesthetics in Aventura. We'll assess your skin and create a personalized treatment plan to restore your clearest, most radiant complexion."]}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-12","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"font-playfair text-xl font-bold text-[#1A1A1A] mb-6","children":"Related Services"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4","children":[["$","$L3","ipl-photofacial",{"href":"/services/ipl-photofacial","className":"bg-warm-white border border-warm-border p-5 rounded-sm hover-lift group block","children":[["$","h4",null,{"className":"font-inter text-sm font-semibold text-[#1A1A1A] group-hover:text-gold transition-colors mb-1","children":"IPL Stellar M22"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"font-inter text-xs text-warm-gray line-clamp-2","children":"The gold standard in IPL technology — target sun damage, redness, vascular lesions, and uneven skin tone with the Lumenis Stellar M22."}]]}],["$","$L3","resurfx",{"href":"/services/resurfx","className":"bg-warm-white border border-warm-border p-5 rounded-sm hover-lift group block","children":[["$","h4",null,{"className":"font-inter text-sm font-semibold text-[#1A1A1A] group-hover:text-gold transition-colors mb-1","children":"ResurFX"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"font-inter text-xs text-warm-gray line-clamp-2","children":"Non-ablative fractional laser for skin resurfacing, scars, stretch marks, and texture improvement."}]]}]]}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"lg:col-span-1","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"sticky top-28 space-y-6","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-[#1A1A1A] p-6 rounded-sm","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"font-playfair text-lg font-bold text-white mb-2","children":"Ready to Get Started?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"font-inter text-sm text-white/60 mb-4","children":"Book your free consultation at Kami Aesthetics in Aventura."}],["$","a",null,{"href":"https://book.squareup.com/appointments/ikr1wg4h4cumcw/location/LK1V8GFYJGAS7/services","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer","children":["$","button",null,{"className":"inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 whitespace-nowrap font-medium ring-offset-background focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2 disabled:pointer-events-none disabled:opacity-50 [&_svg]:pointer-events-none [&_svg]:size-4 [&_svg]:shrink-0 h-10 px-4 w-full bg-gold hover:bg-gold-dark text-white font-inter text-sm tracking-wider rounded-none py-5 transition-all duration-300","children":["Book Now ",["$","svg",null,{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":24,"height":24,"viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":2,"strokeLinecap":"round","stro